        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Aggregate all concrete annotation types into a single namespace for use by readers and converters. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Re-export of all concrete annotation classes (bold, italic, size, color, etc.). \par \b Input\/ \:  None (package-level imports). \par \b Output\/ \:  Unified <bold>all</bold> list containing all annotation symbols. \par \b Links\/ \:  [EXPORTS(10): AlignmentAnnotation, AttachAnnotation, BBoxAnnotation, BoldAnnotation, ColorAnnotation, ConfidenceAnnotation, IndentationAnnotation, ItalicAnnotation, LinkedTextAnnotation, SizeAnnotation, SpacingAnnotation, StrikeAnnotation, StyleAnnotation, SubscriptAnnotation, SuperscriptAnnotation, TableAnnotation, UnderlinedAnnotation, ReferenceAnnotation] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>all</bold> includes all 18 concrete annotation types \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why separate concrete_annotations from the base Annotation? A: Clean separation of base class from its implementations, enabling independent evolution. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
